<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-497] Logger (Category) names don&apos;t follow common pattern</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-497</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>The Wire class uses two loggers named unexpected. The &amp;quot;org.apache.commons.&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
prefix is missing - so you can&amp;#39;t mute all debug level statements with a&lt;br/&gt;
one-liner in you log4j.properties for example:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;log4j.logger.org.apache.commons.httpclient INFO&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
You have to add this, too:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;log4j.logger.httpclient INFO&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Please prepend the &amp;quot;org.apache.commons.&amp;quot; before both names.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
Christian&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
class Wire {&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static Wire HEADER_WIRE = new&lt;br/&gt;
Wire(LogFactory.getLog(&amp;quot;httpclient.wire.header&amp;quot;));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;public static Wire CONTENT_WIRE = new&lt;br/&gt;
Wire(LogFactory.getLog(&amp;quot;httpclient.wire.content&amp;quot;));&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/jakarta/commons/proper/httpclient/trunk/src/java/org/apache/commons/httpclient/Wire.java?rev=155418&amp;view=markup&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/jakarta/commons/proper/httpclient/trunk/src/java/org/apache/commons/httpclient/Wire.java?rev=155418&amp;amp;view=markup&lt;/a&gt;</description>
                <environment>Operating System: other&lt;br/&gt;
Platform: All</environment>
